sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_script_fix"><sys_script_fix action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><before>false</before><description/><flush_cache>false</flush_cache><name>Create Stories to replicate behaviour</name><record_for_rollback>false</record_for_rollback><run_once>true</run_once><script><![CDATA[replicate("1771a6e207568410944dfc018c1ed0b6", 7, 350);

function replicate (source, nstart, niterations){
	var fields = "project,theme,product,priority,type,story_points,short_description,acceptance_criteria,description,assignment_group,correlation_id,release,epic,assigned_to";
	var fieldsDup = fields.split(',');

	var current = new GlideRecord("rm_story");
	// ID from the story
	current.get(source);

	var count = nstart;
	while (count < niterations){
	var gr = new GlideRecord('rm_story');
		gr.initialize();
		for(i=0;i<fieldsDup.length;i++){
			if(fieldsDup[i]=='short_description')
				gr.setValue(fieldsDup[i],current.getValue(fieldsDup[i])+' ' + count);
			else {
				if(fieldsDup[i]=='description')
					gr.setValue(fieldsDup[i],current.getValue(fieldsDup[i])+' ' + count);
				else
					gr.setValue(fieldsDup[i],current.getValue(fieldsDup[i]));
			}
		}
		var newid = gr.insert();
		count ++;
		gs.info("We insert " + count);
		GlideSysAttachment.copy('rm_story',current.sys_id,'rm_story',newid);
	}

}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script_fix</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-01-15 15:01:53</sys_created_on><sys_id>c7463eea07968410944dfc018c1ed0ac</sys_id><sys_mod_count>3</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Create Stories to replicate behaviour</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_fix_c7463eea07968410944dfc018c1ed0ac</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-15 15:10:22</sys_updated_on><unloadable>false</unloadable></sys_script_fix></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: sysevent_script_action_d92636b2975301008e00958e3b297567
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sysevent_script_action"><sysevent_script_action action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>false</active><condition_script/><description/><event_name>login.failed</event_name><name>SNC User Lockout Check with Auto Unlock</name><order>100</order><script><![CDATA[//
// Check to see if the user has failed to login too many times
// when the limit is reached, lock the user out of the system.
// Also create a trigger to unlock the user after 'N' minutes.
//

lockoutOnFailedLogin();

function lockoutOnFailedLogin() {
	var maxUnlockAttempts = gs.getProperty("glide.user.max_unlock_attempts", 5);
	var gr = new GlideRecord("sys_user");
	if (gr.get("user_name", event.parm1.toString())) {
		if (gr.failed_attempts > maxUnlockAttempts)
			return;

		gr.failed_attempts += 1;
		if (gr.failed_attempts > maxUnlockAttempts) {
			gr.locked_out = true;
			gr.update();
			gs.log("User " + event.parm1 + " locked out due to too many invalid login attempts");
			triggerUnlock(gr.sys_id);
		} else {
			gr.update();       
		}
	}
}

function triggerUnlock(userSysID) {
	var unlockIn = gs.getProperty("glide.user.unlock_timeout_in_mins", 15);
	var trigger = new GlideRecord("sys_trigger");
	trigger.name = "Unlock the user after "+ unlockIn + " mins";
	trigger.next_action = getTriggerTime(unlockIn);
	trigger.job_id.setDisplayValue('RunScriptJob');
	trigger.script = getTriggerScript(userSysID);
	trigger.document = 'sys_user';
	trigger.document_key = userSysID;
	trigger.state = 0;
	trigger.trigger_type = 0;
	trigger.insert();
}

function getTriggerScript(userSysID) {
	var ret = ""
	+ "var gr = new GlideRecord('sys_user');\n"
	+ "gr.addQuery('sys_id', '" +userSysID+ "');\n"
	+ "gr.addQuery('locked_out', true);\n"
	+ "gr.query();\n"
	+ "if (gr.next()) {\n"
		+ "gr.locked_out = false;\n"
		+ "gr.failed_attempts = 0;\n"
		+ "gr.update();\n"
		+ "gs.log('Auto-unlocking user '+gr.name);\n"
	+ "} else {\n"
		+ "gs.log('Unable to auto-unlock user with sys_id: "+userSysID+"');\n"
	+ "}";
	return ret;
}

function getTriggerTime(minutesToAdd) {
	var checkTime = new GlideDateTime(/*now*/);
	checkTime.addSeconds(minutesToAdd * 60);
	return checkTime;
}
]]></script><synchronous>true</synchronous><sys_class_name>sysevent_script_action</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2013-08-24 00:27:47</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>d92636b2975301008e00958e3b297567</sys_id><sys_mod_count>28</sys_mod_count><sys_name>SNC User Lockout Check with Auto Unlock</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="High Security Settings" source="com.glide.high_security">a9e7329d07c20010944dfc018c1ed0a7</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sysevent_script_action_d92636b2975301008e00958e3b297567</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2019-12-30 08:44:38</sys_updated_on></sysevent_script_action></record_update>
